    {
     "type": "html",
     "name": "certMessage",
     "html": {
      "default": "By filing a weekly claim, you are requesting an Unemployment Insurance (UI) benefit payment. It is important that you answer all questions accurately and truthfully. You are legally responsible for the information reported on your weekly claim.\n<br><br>\nThe information you enter on this application will be saved until 11:59 p.m. on Saturday <<filingRequestWeekSaturday>>, if you do not submit this application today.\n<br><br>\nYou will be logged out of the application if there is no activity for <<continuedClaimTimeoutMinutes>> minutes. \n<br><br>\nYou must file your weekly claim application Sunday through Friday to request benefits for the previous week. If you do not file your weekly claim within the allowed 6 days, you are denied benefits for that week. You must file a new claim application to reactivate your claim and begin filing weekly claims again.\n<br><br>\nPreparing to file your weekly claim:\n<br><br>\n<ul>\n<li>You will be asked about the pay you've received and earned the previous week (ex: wages, holiday, vacation, pension, severance pay, and workers' compensation)</li>\n<li>You will be asked for the following information regarding your work searches, if applicable</li>\n<ul>\n<li>Date you applied for the job</li>\n<li>Company name</li>\n<li>Company address, website or email address</li>\n<li>The job for which you applied</li>\n</ul>\n</ul>\nWARNING:\n<br><br>\nIf you withhold or provide false information to increase or collect UI benefits, you are committing fraud. Fraudulently collecting UI benefits is a serious offense and will be investigated. If you have an overpayment as a result of fraudulent claim activity, you will not receive UI benefits until you have paid your debt in full.\n",
      "es": "[ES] By filing a weekly claim, you are requesting an Unemployment Insurance (UI) benefit payment. It is important that you answer all questions accurately and truthfully. You are legally responsible for the information reported on your weekly claim.\n<br><br>\nThe information you enter on this application will be saved until 11:59 p.m. on Saturday <<filingRequestWeekSaturday>>, if you do not submit this application today.\n<br><br>\nYou will be logged out of the application if there is no activity for <<continuedClaimTimeoutMinutes>> minutes. \n<br><br>\nYou must file your weekly claim application Sunday through Friday to request benefits for the previous week. If you do not file your weekly claim within the allowed 6 days, you are denied benefits for that week. You must file a new claim application to reactivate your claim and begin filing weekly claims again.\n<br><br>\nPreparing to file your weekly claim:\n<br><br>\n<ul>\n<li>You will be asked about the pay you've received and earned the previous week (ex: wages, holiday, vacation, pension, severance pay, and workers' compensation)</li>\n<li>You will be asked for the following information regarding your work searches, if applicable</li>\n<ul>\n<li>Date you applied for the job</li>\n<li>Company name</li>\n<li>Company address, website or email address</li>\n<li>The job for which you applied</li>\n</ul>\n</ul>\nWARNING:\n<br><br>\nIf you withhold or provide false information to increase or collect UI benefits, you are committing fraud. Fraudulently collecting UI benefits is a serious offense and will be investigated. If you have an overpayment as a result of fraudulent claim activity, you will not receive UI benefits until you have paid your debt in full.\n"
     }
    }
