      {
       "type": "html",
       "name": "contactReporting",
       "html": {
        "default": "You must report a minimum of two (2) work search contacts each week. \n<ul>\n  <li>Employer contacts must be made between Sunday and Saturday of the week for which you are filing a claim</li>\n<li>Your work search must be a reasonable and honest effort to find suitable work</li>\n<li>You must be willing to accept a reasonable wage in your area for the job for which you applied </li>\n<li>A repeat or follow-up work search for the same position with one employer can be made after six weeks from the initial contact </li>\n</ul>\nYou may be denied benefits if you fail to:\n<ul>\n<li>Make a minimum of two work searches during each week you are claimant benefits</li>\n<li>Submit a record of the work searches upon request</li>\n<li>However, if you started new employment during the week, you are only required to report a minimum of one (1) work search contact. This contact must be in addition to the employer for whom you began working.</li>\n<ul>",
        "es": "[ES] You must report a minimum of two (2) work search contacts each week. \n<ul>\n  <li>Employer contacts must be made between Sunday and Saturday of the week for which you are filing a claim</li>\n<li>Your work search must be a reasonable and honest effort to find suitable work</li>\n<li>You must be willing to accept a reasonable wage in your area for the job for which you applied </li>\n<li>A repeat or follow-up work search for the same position with one employer can be made after six weeks from the initial contact </li>\n</ul>\nYou may be denied benefits if you fail to:\n<ul>\n<li>Make a minimum of two work searches during each week you are claimant benefits</li>\n<li>Submit a record of the work searches upon request</li>\n<li>However, if you started new employment during the week, you are only required to report a minimum of one (1) work search contact. This contact must be in addition to the employer for whom you began working.</li>\n<ul>You must report a minimum of two (2) work search contacts each week. \n<ul>\n  <li>Employer contacts must be made between Sunday and Saturday of the week for which you are filing a claim</li>\n<li>Your work search must be a reasonable and honest effort to find suitable work</li>\n<li>You must be willing to accept a reasonable wage in your area for the job for which you applied </li>\n<li>A repeat or follow-up work search for the same position with one employer can be made after six weeks from the initial contact </li>\n</ul>\nYou may be denied benefits if you fail to:\n<ul>\n<li>Make a minimum of two work searches during each week you are claimant benefits</li>\n<li>Submit a record of the work searches upon request</li>\n<li>However, if you started new employment during the week, you are only required to report a minimum of one (1) work search contact. This contact must be in addition to the employer for whom you began working.</li>\n<ul>"
       }
